    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just don't have the money for the clinic right now and it's so late anyway. i was looking at this forum and they were saying if you use a thick layer of honey and then use some medical tape to seal the edges together, it basically acts like a natural glue and keeps everything closed so you don't need the stitches. if i do that, it should be fine to just sleep it off and see how it looks in the morning, right? it's not like i'm losing a lot of blood, it's just a slow ooze.",
